name: quality
description: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

name: increased sensitivity to irradiation
description: A sensitivity to irradiation which is relatively high.

name: increased tonicity
description: A tonicity which is relatively high.

name: obsolete plant growth hormone sensitivity value
medium acidity
description: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.

name: has extra parts of type
description: The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.

name: increased resistance to
description: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively high.

name: anaerobic (for occurrence)
description: A sensitivity of a process inhering in a biological process by virtue of the process unfolding in a location without oxygen.

name: shortened
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably lower than its width.

name: desaturated cyan
description: A color consisting of cyan colour and low saturation.

name: misaligned away from
description: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in a improper spatial positioning away from an additional entity.

name: phototoxic
description: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being susceptible to damage by light.

name: decreased variability of color
description: A variability of color which is relatively low.

name: saddle-shaped
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's similarity to the appearance of a saddle.

name: male fertility
description: A fertility quality of inhering in a male by virtue of the bearer's disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction.

name: refractile
description: A reflectivity quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to refract light.

name: increased angle to
description: An angle which is relatively high.

name: dorsal to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the back or upper surface of an organism relative to another entity.

name: radiopaque
description: A readiopacity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's prevention of the passage of electromagnetic radiation.

name: susceptibility toward
description: A quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer's propensity to resist an external stimulus.

name: unserrated
description: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

name: splayed
description: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outward.

name: depth
description: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

name: posterior orientation
description: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posteriorly.

name: irregularly shaped
description: A shape quality inhering on a bearer by virtue of a bearer's shape lacking in pattern or uniformity; for example, it may have sides of different lengths, different curvatures, or unequal angles.

name: rhomboid
description: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being oval and a little angular in the middle.

name: invaginated
description: A shape quality in which a portion of the outermost boundary of an entity folds in space such that a portion that was originally convex is now concave.

name: lacking processual parts
description: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a processual part as specified by the additional entity.

name: inconspicuous
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being clearly visible.

name: erose
description: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an irregularly toothed edge.

name: confluent with
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer flowing or coming together with another entity.

name: fertility
description: A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

name: resistant to
description: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to a stimulus.

name: neoplastic, non-invasive
description: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition not to invade surrounding tissues.

name: brochidodromous
description: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having secondary branches joined together in a series of prominent arches.

name: dystrophic
description: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormally developed, usually due to malnutrition.

name: overlap with
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's coinciding spatially, partially or wholly with another entity.

name: distal orientation
description: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed distally.

name: bent
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one or more angle(s) in its length.

name: recurrent
description: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurring or appearing again or repeatedly.

name: biological sex
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

name: opposite
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned on opposite sides on the same plane.

name: decreased width
description: A width which is relatively small.

name: decreased radioactivity
description: A radioactivity which is relatively high.

name: increased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
description: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is higher than normal or average.

name: leaf-like
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's similarity to the appearance of a leaf.

name: stacked
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned with multiple entities of the same type above and below.

name: normal fatigability
description: A fatigability which is relatively normal or average

name: stepped
description: Having a shape or form that resembles a step of a stairway (e.g., a ledge or offset margin).

name: behavioural inactive
description: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to lack activity.

name: focus
description: An optical quality where light rays originating from a point on the object converge.

name: auxotrophic
description: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

name: normal male fertility
description: A male fertility which is relatively normal or average.

name: bowl shaped
description: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of a bowl.

name: sigmoid
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of two curves, in opposite directions. S-shaped.

name: increased elevation
description: An elevation which is relatively high.

name: decondensed
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being thinner or more losely packed.

name: phosphorylation
description: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the addition of a phosphate (PO4) group to the bearer.

name: decreased affinity
description: An affinity which is relatively low.

name: normal volume
description: A volume which is relatively normal or average

name: decreased humidity
description: An decrease in humidity.

name: disorganized
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking organisation.

name: mature
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting complete growth, differentiation, or development.

name: right
description: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces west.

name: non-functional
description: A disfunctional quality held by the bearer when the latter is unable to perform a regular function(s).

name: focally extensive
description: Single lesion with expansion into surrounding tissue.

name: right angle to
description: An angle which is 90 degrees to another entity.

name: L-shaped
description: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter L.

name: ipsilateral to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being on the same side in relation to another structure.

name: normal fluorescence
description: A fluorescence which is relatively normal or average.

name: plush
description: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered or partially covered with hair that has increased thickness and softness.

name: cylindrical
description: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a consistently-sized round cross section.

name: increased magnetism
description: A magnetism which is relatively high.

name: subcircular
description: A circular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being nearly, but not perfectly, circular.

name: catalytic activity
description: A physical quality inhering in a catalyst by virtue of the amount of the catalyst's action.

name: congested
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer with some kind of aperture or opening that is blocked or clogged.

name: protruding out of
description: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity.

name: exposed
description: Open to view or not covered by another entity.

name: anaerobic
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's independence on oxygen.

name: desaturated blue
description: A color consisting of blue hue and low saturation.

name: beige
description: A colour that is very pale yellowish brown.

name: phosphorylated
description: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer's having a phosphate (PO4) group.

name: specificity to
description: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability of a probe to react precisely with a specific target molecule.

name: diagonal to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located on a sloping line joining two nonconsecutive points of an entity relative to another entity.

name: sparse
description: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being scattered; spread irregularly, and at a distance from each other.

name: tolerant to
description: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its disposition to endure or being insensitive to a stimulus.

name: sharp
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's terminating in a point or edge.

name: high saturation
description: A color saturation which is of high purity.

name: increased female fertility
description: A female fertility which is relatively high.

name: obsolete edematous (sensu botany)
description: An extended swelling in plant organs caused primarily by an excessive accumulation of water.

name: inactive
description: A quality of a physical object that is currently realizing none of its functions.

name: dark red
description: A color consisting of red hue and low brightness.

name: drooping
description: To bent or hang downwards.

name: surrounded by
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being enclosed on all sides by another entity.

name: rough
description: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's irregular surface.

name: decreased life span
description: A life span which is relatively low.

name: concealed
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being hidden from view.

name: superelliptic
description: A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt

name: green
description: A color hue with medium-low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between yellow and blue, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 490 to 570 nanometers.

name: serous
description: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing or resembling serum.

name: strain
description: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the relative change in the bearer's length or the bearer's volume when being stretched or squashed.

name: convolute
description: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's one edge of its surface being wholly rolled up in another.

name: increased flexibility
description: A flexibility which is relatively high.

name: variability of rate

name: cellular quality
description: A monadic quality of continuant that exists at the cellular level of organisation.

name: spur shaped
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing a small, spike-like shape.

name: cauline to

name: continuous with

name: variability of shape
description: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits shape variation or change.

name: radiation quality
description: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

name: hypoplastic
description: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced number of cells within an organ or tissue.

name: increased sensitivity toward
description: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is higher than normal/average.

name: pubescent
description: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having arrived at the onset of puberty (the age at which sex glands become functional) but not yet fully mature.

name: rugose
description: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having many wrinkles or creases on the surface.

name: posterolateral orientation
description: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posterolaterally.

name: telescopic
description: Having or resembling the shape of a telescope.

name: minimal
description: Being smallest in amount, extent or degree.

name: in contact with
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's touching another entity.

name: decreased contractility
description: A contractility which is relatively low.

name: parallel-sided
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing two sides that are at the same continuous distance relative to each other.

name: mosaic trisomy
description: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having extra chromosomal material in only some of it's cells.

name: areolate
description: A surface feature shape inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer's being divided by ridge-like structures into a number of small, irregular spaces.

name: closed
description: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording blocked passage or view.

name: south
description: South is one of the four cardinal directions or compass points. South is the polar opposite of north and is perpendicular to east and west.

name: mislocalised medially
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards the middle of an organism.

name: semi-deciduous(plant)
description: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.

name: dysplastic
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting an alteration in size, shape or organization of its constituent cells.

name: flexible
description: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

name: oriented towards
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being aligned or positioned towards another entity.

name: translucent
description: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting low opacity.

name: pointed
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a point.

name: dense
description: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting density.

name: stratified
description: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.

name: amount
description: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

name: normal anterior-posterior diameter
description: An anterior-posterior diameter which is relatively normal or average

name: prominence
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which the bearers stands out or projects beyond a surface or line.

name: poorly ossified
description: A quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing only minor levels of ossification.

name: disrupted
description: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being interrupted of its normal course.

name: square
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an equal-sided rectangular form.

name: severe increased temperature
description: A temperature which is increased by a high degree.

name: concentration of
description: A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

name: normal female receptivity
description: A female receptivity which is relatively normal or average.

name: symmetry
description: A pattern quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the correspondence in size, shape, and relative position of the bearer's parts on opposite sides of a dividing line or median plane or about a center or axis.

name: pathological
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormal and having a destructive effect on living tissue.

name: specific volume
description: A volume quality inhering in a mass of substance by virtue of the amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

name: hypotrophic
description: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced size of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).

name: moderate intensity
description: An intensity which is less than extreme in type or degree or effect or force.

name: radiation emitting quality
description: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to emit radiation.

name: level with
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located at the same level as another entity.

name: platelike
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

name: columnar
description: A shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being elongated and cylindrical.

name: normal area
description: An area which is relatively normal or average

name: process efficacy
description: The ability of a process to produce its output.

name: complexity
description: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

name: friable
description: Easily reduced to powder or easily fragmentable or crumbly.

name: increased duration of temperature
description: A duration of temperature which is greater relative to the normal or average in respect to the quality of temperature of enduring or continuing in time.

name: ubiquinated
description: A molecular quality that pertains to the post-translational modification of a protein by the covalent attachment of one or more ubiquitin monomer.

name: non-progressive
description: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not increasing over time.

name: normal distance
description: A distance which is relatively normal or average.

name: uncoordinated
description: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

name: catalytic (activity) concentration
description: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's catalytic activity divided by the volume of the system.

name: decreased spatial extent of a process
description: A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a smaller length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.

name: recent
description: A quality of a process which occurs near to or not long before the present.

name: pedunculate
description: Being supported by a peduncle or stalk.

name: radiation reflective quality
description: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to scatter or reflect radiation.

name: quality of a substance
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

name: pseudohermaphrodite
description: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

name: necessity of occurrent
description: A quality of single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer is essential or indispensable.

name: calcified
description: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's being encrusted or impregnated with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311).

name: light deep pink
description: Pink color having high brightness and moderate saturation.

name: random pattern
description: characterised by an unidentifiable pattern.

name: ventralized
description: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some or all of what are normally dorsal structures.

name: recurved
description: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved backward or inward.

name: conical
description: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a cone (a 3-D shape with a round cross section that tapers).

name: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type
description: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.

name: decreased waxiness
description: A waxiness which is relatively low.

name: electric charge
description: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the overall electric charge of the molecule, which is due to a comparison between the total number of electrons and the total number of protons.

name: wetness
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

name: unresponsive to
description: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

name: anterior to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the front of an organism relative to another entity.

name: boomerang shaped
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape like a boomerang, with two arms connected at an angle.

name: wholeness
description: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer includes all its components.

name: snowman-shaped
description: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two connected parts, roughly spherical, of different sizes.

name: light grey
description: A color consisting of grey color and high brightness.

name: laterally rotated
description: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the side of an organism.

name: unicellular
description: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of exactly one cell.

name: hypsodont
description: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having dentition characterized by high-crowned teeth and enamel which extends far past the gum line, which provides extra material for wear and tear.

name: dark phase
description: A phase which occurs during dark cycle.

name: anucleate

name: fiber shaped
description: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a consistently sized and approximately round cross-section along its length, which is many times larger than its diameter.

name: hydropic

name: pressure
description: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of force per unit area it exerts.

name: decreased variability of size
description: A variability of size which is relatively low.

name: increased permeability
description: A permeability which is relatively high.

name: disomy
description: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing only two chromosome from a pair in a cell's nucleus.

name: tomentose
description: A quality of being covered with short, dense, matted hairs.

name: splayed dorsal
description: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards from the back or upper surface of an organism.

name: normal sensitivity of a process to oxygen
description: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is relatively normal.

name: pear shaped
description: Having the shape of a pear; tapering near the top and bulging toward the base or bottom. From thefreedictionary.com

name: wholly ventralized
description: A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally ventral structures.

name: unipotent
description: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce only one differentiated cell type.

name: increased process quality
description: A quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

name: pilosity

name: fatty

name: damage

name: viscous

name: distichous

name: terminal

name: tetraploid

name: decreased branchiness

name: hyperresponsive to
description: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's excessive reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

name: neoplastic, non-malignant
description: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition not to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

name: oblate
description: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting an equatorial diameter greater than its polar diameter.

name: normal duration
description: A duration quality of a process which is relatively normal.

name: anterodorsal to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the front and upper surface of an organism relative to another entity.

name: increased male receptivity

name: profound intensity

name: prostrate

name: dappled

name: h minus

name: unpigmented

name: emmision wavelength

name: normal resistance to
description: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively normal or average

name: parous

name: lumenized

name: increased velocity

name: biscupidate

name: subacute

name: coiled

name: increased variability of temperature
description: A variability of temperature which is relatively high.

name: plume-shaped
description: A shape that ineres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's mass being distributed in a feather-like fashion.

name: sterile

name: folded

name: female receptivity

name: hard

name: firm

name: behavioral quality of a process

name: perpendicular to
description: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located at a right angle relative to another entity.

name: hermaphrodite

name: mass flow rate

name: laterally compressed

name: parallelogram
description:
A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:
1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.
2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.
3. The diagonals bisect each other.
4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.
5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)
6.It possesses rotational symmetry.
7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.
8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a somewhat elongated form with approximately parallel sides.

name: disconnected
description: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.

name: front
description: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the south when it faces north.

name: 3-D extent
description: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions.

name: sound frequency
description: The frequency of transmitted vibrations.

name: divergent from
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two or more entities that extend from a common point in different directions.

name: behavioral quality
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

name: flavourless
description: A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking flavour.

name: emarginate
description: A notched shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a notched tip or edge.

name: trapezoid
description: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being a quadrilateral with two parallel sides.

name: normal mobility
description: A mobility which is relatively normal or average.

name: dorsomedial orientation
description: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsomedially.

name: limaciform
description: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a slug.

name: viable
description: A viability quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer's ability to survive or the long term survival ability of a given population.

name: rate of occurence
description: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

name: convex 3-D shape
description: A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.

name: vacuolated
description: A structural quality inhering in a cytoplasm that contains fluid filled cavities.

name: irregular rhythm
description: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking rhythm lacking pattern.

name: osmolarity
description: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.

name: monstrous
description: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's all-encompassing, grotesque morphological defects.

name: multiparous
description: A viviparous organism that has given birth two or more times.

name: saturated magenta
description: A color consisting of magenta color and high saturation.

name: mislocalised proximally
description: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards to point of attachment or origin.
